==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|riden}}, Old English {{term|ridan|rīdan}}, from Germanic *{{term||ridanan}}, from Indo-European *{{term||reidh-}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|rijden}}, German {{term|reiten}}, Swedish {{term|rida}}; and (''from Indo-European'') with Welsh {{term|rhwyddhau||hurry}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɹaɪd/}}, {{SAMPA|/r\aId/}}
* {{audio|en-us-ride.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪd}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|rides|riding|rode|ridden}}

# To [[transport]] oneself by means of a [[bicycle]], [[horse]], etc.
# To sit on and control an animal for [[sport]] or [[recreation]].
# To be carried or supported by something with [[momentum]].
# {{lacrosse}} To play [[defense]] on the defensemen or midfielders, as an attackman.
# {{informal}} To [[copulate]] while sexually mounted on; have [[sexual intercourse]] with (a woman). <!--since 1250-->
# To [[obsess]]; to [[nag]].

